					<head>Esther scroll</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n79053644" rend="visible">
						<summary>The Book of Esther. </summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="1r" to="1r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Megilat Ester </title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מגלת אסתר</title>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Leather scroll of the 15th to 16th century. </p>
						<objectDesc form="scroll ">
							<supportDesc material="leather">
								<support>Leather. </support>
								<extent>5 membranes, 16 columns. <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>260</height>
										<width>3140</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<collation>
									<p>5 membranes, with leather strap. </p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Leather often fibrous on verso. </p>
									<p>First column of text darker and difficult to read. </p>
									<p>Strap broken off short. </p>
									<p>Cockling/creasing and vertical marks from rolling. </p>
									<p>Surface occasionally disturbed by erasures. </p>
									<p>Slight worming at edges. </p>
									<p>A few tears, losses, and edges rolling over.  </p>
									<p>Crease between text columns.  </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="16" ruledLines="22" writtenLines="22">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Ruling by hard point,
membrane by membrane.</p>
									<p>Visible stiching of membranes. </p>
									<p>Three tagin on שעטנזגץ, and one on בדהחיק. </p>
									<p>The first letters of verse 4 marked by dots to indicate the Tetragrammaton.</p>
									<p>A few majuscular or minuscular letters. </p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
